  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Integrating Healthcare in Resilience Building in Liben zone</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Direct beneficiaries are pastoralist and agropastorlaist HHs. who are the most vulnerable people in Dhekasuftu and Dolo-Ado woredas in Liben zone of Somali region.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Drought has caused a decline in agriculture and livestock production severely affecting food and livelihood security in Liben Zone. Next to drought, human and livestock disease and resource-based conflict are identified as major challenges. Infrastructure and access to social services is inadequate in the targeted districts. This project is complementary to the resilience building project RESET.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Goal: integrating healthcare into resilience building in communities of 35 kebeles of four woredas (districts) in Liben Zone, strengthening the capacity of communities to cope with recurring droughts 
Objectives:
&#x2022; To equip 60 health professionals with Integrated Risk Management (IRM) knowledge and Participatory Health Risk Assessment (PHRA) skills.
&#x2022; Communities and their health facilities implement Health Risk Reduction (HRR) action plans 
&#x2022; Communities can respond to health and related (nutrition) emergencies
&#x2022; To reduce the impact of climate change induced recurrent drought on health.</narrative>
  </description>
